Key Match Events: Maximilian Beier made his senior international debut for Germany.
Beier hit the inside of the post with his very first touch.
Manuel Neuer's 89th minute gaffe went unpunished due to an offside flag.
Pre-Game Insights: Julian Nagelsmann did not have his full squad available due to some players being involved in the Champions League final.
Post-Match Reflections: Beier's performance has given Nagelsmann a selection headache, potentially vindicating the exclusion of Timo Werner and Serge Gnabry.
Kai Havertz was outshone by Beier and may not be considered a starter for Euro 2024.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Germany will play another warm-up friendly against Greece on June 7.
Germany will open Euro 2024 against Scotland in Munich.
